raditional-style rooms with a community bathroom on each floor  cluster-style rooms are a combination of single and double occupancy units which share a small cluster bathroom within their own private suite  suite style is the same as a cluster with the addition of a shared living space  apartment-style units provide everyone with their own private bedroom, sharing the common spaces within the unit   Each room is equipped with a twin bed, desk, and chair for each participant. Wheelchair accessible rooms are also available upon request. For more information on our various residence halls, explore our website further in order to view photos of the different buildings and housing options we have available to offer.  Individual rooms are cleaned prior to a group’s arrival. It is the responsibility of all conference guests to keep the units cleaned.  However, our housekeeping staff perform daily cleaning of public areas and community bathrooms. Additional housekeeping services may be pre-arranged for an additional fee.      Summer 2020 Conferences - Nightly Rates       Nightly Rates (per person)   Long-Term (per person - staying 28 days or longer)       Single Student Residence (apartment-style unit)  $59 (single occupancy)  Single Student Residence (apartment-style unit)  $40 (single occupancy)    Academic & Residential Complex (ARC)  $55 (traditional double), $65 (semi-suite double), $70 (semi-suite single)  Academic & Residential Complex (ARC)  $50 (traditional double), $60 (semi-suite double), $70 (semi-suite single)    James Stukel Towers (suite-style unit)  $45 (double occupancy), $59 (single occupancy)  James Stukel Towers (suite-style unit)  $31 (double occupancy), $40 (single occupancy)    Thomas Beckham & Marie Robinson Hall 
